# ReactWoo Flow

## Product boundary

- Internal WordPress **orchestration platform** for intake, triage, specifications, agent routing, and release coordination.
- Does **not** replace Jira, GitHub, or Cursor. Does **not** execute development work remotely (Cursor MCP is prepare-only until bridge ships).
- Single CPT: `rwf_item`. All item data in post meta (`_rwf_*`).

## Code conventions

- Provider adapters implement `RWF_Provider_Interface` in `includes/providers/`.
- Agent workflows go through `RWF_Agent::execute()` — never call OpenAI/Anthropic directly from admin or REST.
- Prompt templates are Markdown files in `prompts/`; reference by filename in agent args.
- Capabilities: `edit_rwf_items`, `manage_rwf` — not generic `edit_posts`.
- Plugin install folder: `reactwoo-flow/` inside repo root.

## MVP scope (do not expand without plan update)

In scope: dashboard, inbox, item CRUD, environment capture, attachments, AI triage, specs, release notes, handoff prep, REST context export, intake shortcode.

Out of scope until planned: Jira/GitHub/Confluence integration, Cursor MCP execution, Playwright QA, UX agent pipeline.

## After implementation

Update `CHANGELOG.md` + `PLAN.md`, bump `RWF_VERSION` and plugin header, commit, tag `v*`, push. Tag push triggers CI publish; skip local zip unless needed immediately.
